1
00:00:48,923 --> 00:00:50,133
Who were you with?

2
00:00:52,635 --> 00:00:55,180
Never mind. I'm sorry.

3
00:01:17,494 --> 00:01:18,870
What did you do today?

4
00:01:20,163 --> 00:01:21,539
I waited for you.

5
00:01:29,339 --> 00:01:30,340
I'm sorry.

6
00:01:31,674 --> 00:01:32,675
I'm late.

7
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:05,667
What are you doing?

8
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:10,672
I'll leave now.

9
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:11,714
What?

10
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:14,425
I won't come here anymore.

11
00:02:22,475 --> 00:02:23,768
What are you saying?

12
00:02:23,852 --> 00:02:24,853
I'm fine

13
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:27,856
now.

14
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:30,024
I'll break up with you.

15
00:02:34,112 --> 00:02:37,866
Then why were you here all along?

16
00:02:38,575 --> 00:02:39,993
I thought

17
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:44,164
you'd give me a warm hug
for the last time.

18
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:53,006
So,

19
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:56,551
are you happy now?

20
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:58,595
Yes.

21
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:00,555
Thanks.

22
00:03:00,638 --> 00:03:03,516
Stop it. That's enough.

23
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:07,312
-I'm sorry.
-Don't say that.

24
00:03:07,770 --> 00:03:09,188
I know I'm making it hard for you.

25
00:03:12,108 --> 00:03:13,276
I'll stop.

26
00:03:16,779 --> 00:03:17,780
Bye.

27
00:03:22,744 --> 00:03:24,329
Just what are you doing?

28
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:32,503
Why do you have to be so selfish
until the end?

29
00:03:32,837 --> 00:03:34,672
After giving me such a hard time...

30
00:03:35,381 --> 00:03:37,300
You put me through the breakup,

31
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,844
and you came back after everything.

32
00:03:41,137 --> 00:03:43,348
After struggling for a few days,

33
00:03:44,432 --> 00:03:45,767
you're fine now?

34
00:03:46,851 --> 00:03:50,438
Why do you have to do everything
your way all the time?

35
00:03:55,818 --> 00:03:58,154
-I'm sorry.
-For what?

36
00:03:59,322 --> 00:04:02,283
Tell me. What are you sorry for?

37
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:07,664
Why are you doing something to feel
sorry for again?

38
00:04:08,164 --> 00:04:09,207
This happens all the time.

39
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:13,086
Am I a pushover to you?

40
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:19,884
I used to hate it when you yelled.

41
00:04:21,469 --> 00:04:23,513
I guess I made you yell again.

42
00:04:24,514 --> 00:04:28,309
You're not a pushover.

43
00:04:30,812 --> 00:04:31,813
Sorry.

44
00:04:35,858 --> 00:04:37,527
When you first fall in love,

45
00:04:38,069 --> 00:04:41,906
you do so without knowing much
about each other.

46
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:46,911
There are good things and bad things
that you discover.

47
00:04:47,245 --> 00:04:50,623
It's not common to discover
more good things than bad.

48
00:04:54,794 --> 00:04:58,256
And those bad things tend to
have a strong presence.

49
00:04:58,339 --> 00:05:00,883
It's only natural that
you remember them more.

50
00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:04,971
It's kind of obvious
that you feel disappointed.

51
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:09,100
Compromises and falling apart.

52
00:05:09,225 --> 00:05:11,644
The aggressive process of falling apart.

53
00:05:12,353 --> 00:05:14,522
Getting to know more about each other

54
00:05:14,605 --> 00:05:16,691
is like facing a series of variables.

55
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:20,445
Love, in the end,
is about fighting the variables.

56
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:23,990
And so is a drama.

57
00:05:29,871 --> 00:05:33,624
I can't believe there are only
two episodes left.

58
00:05:34,042 --> 00:05:35,251
There's nothing else to watch.

59
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:37,587
Isn't My Country: New Age the next series?

60
00:05:39,505 --> 00:05:41,132
Right. I'm glad.

61
00:05:42,216 --> 00:05:44,719
Why are there only 16 episodes?

62
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:46,971
I wish they made it longer.

63
00:05:47,263 --> 00:05:50,266
Excuse me, what about the writers?

64
00:05:50,349 --> 00:05:53,478
An episode is about 35 pages long.
That adds up to 560 pages in total.

65
00:05:53,561 --> 00:05:55,563
It goes over 600 to count
the proposal and synopsis.

66
00:05:55,646 --> 00:05:57,482
It's endless if you count
the revised scripts.

67
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:00,902
Have you ever broken your wrist
from typing too much?

68
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:04,530
Why are you getting worked up?

69
00:06:06,699 --> 00:06:09,494
I don't know. It just happened.

70
00:06:15,958 --> 00:06:17,668
Actress Jeong Ji-yeon

71
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:19,545
fell off the horse while horse-riding

72
00:06:19,629 --> 00:06:22,673
and broke her leg this afternoon.

73
00:06:22,757 --> 00:06:26,302
Her agency reported that
Ms. Jeong was trying to practice

74
00:06:26,385 --> 00:06:28,638
for a horse-riding scene in her drama

75
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:30,431
and that she fell off the horse.

76
00:06:30,515 --> 00:06:33,935
They also added that she'll have to wear
a cast for over a month.

77
00:06:34,018 --> 00:06:37,730
The drama Ms. Jeong was preparing for
was to be aired on JBC,

78
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:40,483
-a series written by Ms. Jung Hye-jeong.
-What will happen then?

79
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:43,444
-Their time slot will be pushed.
-It was ready to be aired from next week.

80
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:46,280
-The production crew is not thinking of
-What about that slot then?

81
00:06:46,364 --> 00:06:47,365
a replacement.

82
00:06:47,448 --> 00:06:49,033
They announced that

83
00:06:49,117 --> 00:06:52,662
they will postpone shooting indefinitely
until Ms. Jeong recovers.

84
00:07:09,887 --> 00:07:14,559
Hey, stop looking so down.

85
00:07:14,976 --> 00:07:17,061
Isn't this the appropriate face?

86
00:07:19,814 --> 00:07:22,650
-I hurt the lead actress's leg.
-Cut it out.

87
00:07:22,733 --> 00:07:24,694
It's not your fault.

88
00:07:24,777 --> 00:07:26,362
The director is responsible
for everything,

89
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:28,656
but that didn't happen because of you.

90
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:30,992
What? That sounds weird.

91
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:34,245
That's normal. Directors are weird.

92
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:37,248
All the actors and staff will
look at your face on the set.

93
00:07:37,331 --> 00:07:40,418
Because you're the director,
they look at your face and mouth

94
00:07:40,501 --> 00:07:42,712
to see how you feel and what you say.

95
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:44,088
And if you sleep...

96
00:07:45,173 --> 00:07:48,676
You can sleep if you feel tired,
but if you look like a loser,

97
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:52,054
your actors and staff will
feel like a loser too.

98
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:54,849
Don't you know that as a director?

99
00:07:56,434 --> 00:07:57,435
You don't?

100
00:07:57,977 --> 00:07:58,978
Come to my office.

101
00:08:04,108 --> 00:08:05,359
What are you talking about?

102
00:08:05,443 --> 00:08:06,360
Didn't you hear me?

103
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:09,071
I just want to switch the order
of Hwan-dong and your drama.

104
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:10,698
We can't move up the shoot for two months.

105
00:08:10,781 --> 00:08:12,450
We only just got the crew
and cast the actors.

106
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:14,660
The set isn't ready yet.
How can we start shooting?

107
00:08:14,744 --> 00:08:16,162
Shoot outdoors first.

108
00:08:16,245 --> 00:08:17,330
We're not ready at all.

109
00:08:17,413 --> 00:08:19,248
-Get ready as you shoot.
-That's nonsense.

110
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:21,918
What do you suggest then?
The lead actress is hurt and can't shoot.

111
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:24,921
She'll be wearing a cast for a month.
Other actors can start shooting first.

112
00:08:25,004 --> 00:08:28,341
Even after she takes off the cast,
she won't be able to walk properly.

113
00:08:28,424 --> 00:08:30,259
And the lead actress has to appear
in every scene.

114
00:08:30,718 --> 00:08:31,552
It won't work.

115
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:33,221
What about for us?

116
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:35,806
It'll be like going live on air
for us to start shooting now.

117
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:37,934
You've been there and done that. Come on.

118
00:08:38,017 --> 00:08:41,354
Things have changed now.
What about the legal working hours?

119
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:43,689
We can finally work like humans.

120
00:08:43,773 --> 00:08:45,775
Do you want to change the law again?

121
00:08:45,858 --> 00:08:49,237
Do you want to protest
that you want to work 100 hours a week?

122
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:50,821
Don't say such scary things.

123
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:52,573
Can't you see who's scared here?

124
00:08:52,657 --> 00:08:54,992
Whatever. This has been decided
by upper management.

125
00:08:56,452 --> 00:08:59,121
An experienced director like you

126
00:08:59,205 --> 00:09:01,832
should step forward for the company.

127
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:04,585
You used to belittle me
for not getting high ratings.

128
00:09:05,419 --> 00:09:07,129
-I didn't mean it.
-That's too late.

129
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:10,383
I don't know. This isn't going to work.
I can't do it.

130
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:12,677
You say, "I can't do it",
but you'll be getting ready.

131
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:15,096
That's how you become
a part of an organization.

132
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:19,183
Want to make a bet
on whether you'll do it or not?

133
00:09:24,272 --> 00:09:25,398
Damn it.

134
00:09:37,034 --> 00:09:39,495
You're not just a loser.

135
00:09:40,121 --> 00:09:42,081
You just look dead.

136
00:09:42,164 --> 00:09:44,041
Your actors and staff members

137
00:09:44,125 --> 00:09:46,586
will feel like mourners.

138
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:48,254
It's your fault.

139
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:50,631
You made her break her leg.
It's all your fault.

140
00:09:50,715 --> 00:09:53,050
You should've bought her
a horse-riding machine.

141
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:55,928
How could you let her ride a horse?
Don't call yourself a director.

142
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:59,015
Stop staring into the air.
You're a freaking loser.

143
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:13,195
Why did you make the lead actress's hobby
horse-riding?

144
00:10:16,532 --> 00:10:19,869
It could've been something safe
like flower arranging or mowing the grass.

145
00:10:19,952 --> 00:10:23,122
If she's destined to get injured,
mowing the grass could've hurt her too.

146
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:25,916
Have you ever had scrub typhus?

147
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:29,420
Fine. It's actually better
to finish your script

148
00:10:30,254 --> 00:10:31,589
before we shoot.

149
00:10:31,672 --> 00:10:34,550
I'm used to using the viewer's feedback
to fix my script.

150
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:36,886
-How's your writing going?
-I have more time now.

151
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:38,804
-Did you visit Ji-eun at the hospital?
-Yes, I did.

152
00:10:38,888 --> 00:10:39,972
How's Mr. So doing?

153
00:10:40,056 --> 00:10:42,308
Mr. So... What?

154
00:10:42,391 --> 00:10:44,226
What? Why?

155
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:46,228
Why did you bring up Mr. So

156
00:10:46,312 --> 00:10:48,481
when we were talking about the drama?

157
00:10:48,856 --> 00:10:52,193
What? Well, you seem to drink

158
00:10:53,110 --> 00:10:54,195
with him often.

159
00:10:54,278 --> 00:10:55,279
And?

160
00:10:56,739 --> 00:10:58,449
It's good I have more time
to drink with him.

161
00:10:58,532 --> 00:10:59,909
Why would you drink with that guy

162
00:10:59,992 --> 00:11:01,869
when your project is to set off?

163
00:11:01,952 --> 00:11:03,329
What kind of guy do you think he is?

164
00:11:03,412 --> 00:11:04,664
Mr. So.

165
00:11:05,581 --> 00:11:06,957
-Do you like him?
-Of course, I do.

166
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:08,042
Why?

167
00:11:09,293 --> 00:11:10,503
Why would you get angry?

168
00:11:10,586 --> 00:11:12,463
I like him because he's nice to me.

169
00:11:12,713 --> 00:11:13,714
He's nice to you?

170
00:11:14,757 --> 00:11:17,676
He goes around smiling at everyone.

171
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:19,261
That's his job.

172
00:11:19,345 --> 00:11:21,764
Being nice to screenwriters and directors.

173
00:11:21,847 --> 00:11:23,516
That's his job.
Don't you know that already?

174
00:11:23,599 --> 00:11:25,851
-I do know!
-You do?

175
00:11:26,394 --> 00:11:27,478
You know?

176
00:11:27,561 --> 00:11:29,313
Do you still like him
because he's nice to you?

177
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:32,024
Fine. Since you're a successful writer,

178
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:35,111
I guess a lot of people would be
nice to you. Good for you!

179
00:11:35,236 --> 00:11:36,779
Aren't we old and wise enough

180
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:39,156
to have a good judge of character?

181
00:11:39,407 --> 00:11:41,033
Are you just happy that he's nice to you?

182
00:11:41,117 --> 00:11:42,993
Why can't you be nice to me then?

183
00:11:47,331 --> 00:11:48,833
How should we take this?

184
00:11:48,916 --> 00:11:50,584
If Mr. Sung leaves first,

185
00:11:50,876 --> 00:11:52,211
it's just a silly fight.

186
00:11:52,294 --> 00:11:55,131
If Ms. Jung leaves first,
it's a lovers' quarrel.

187
00:11:55,214 --> 00:11:56,715
Something like

188
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:59,135
a woman running away
pretending to be upset.

189
00:11:59,218 --> 00:12:02,555
Like how the guy would go after her
and give her a hug?

190
00:12:03,597 --> 00:12:06,600
Then the woman would hit his chest

191
00:12:06,725 --> 00:12:08,811
and hug him back pretending to give in.

192
00:12:10,146 --> 00:12:11,105
I see.

193
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:27,746
Damn it.

194
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:31,709
How can she talk to the director that way?

195
00:12:31,792 --> 00:12:33,252
Unbelievable!

196
00:12:34,044 --> 00:12:35,045
Damn it!

197
00:12:47,308 --> 00:12:48,559
Honestly?

198
00:12:48,642 --> 00:12:50,811
Yes. Say anything about how you feel

199
00:12:50,895 --> 00:12:52,646
when you work with So-min.

200
00:12:52,730 --> 00:12:55,232
Just tell us how you feel honestly.

201
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:57,902
-Honestly...
-Yes. Honestly.

202
00:12:59,695 --> 00:13:00,696
It's so annoying.

203
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:02,823
Is she going through a rough patch?

204
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:05,784
She's always angry in the car.
But she's not the only one there.

205
00:13:05,868 --> 00:13:07,620
It's really annoying.

206
00:13:08,662 --> 00:13:10,581
You can't be that honest.

207
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:13,501
But you told me to...

208
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,629
Don't tell me this will be aired.

209
00:13:16,712 --> 00:13:19,048
Did you think I filmed this
to keep it for myself?

210
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:22,927
I'm so sorry. Please delete it.

211
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:31,268
You look serious.

212
00:13:32,811 --> 00:13:34,480
The shooting schedule has been moved up.

213
00:13:34,563 --> 00:13:37,149
I don't think that would cause
such a face.

214
00:13:37,441 --> 00:13:38,859
Don't you like the script?

215
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:41,904
-I don't like how Min-jun is.
-What?

216
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:44,907
He's flirting with the actress
he's managing.

217
00:13:46,534 --> 00:13:49,411
What is this? You sound very serious,

218
00:13:50,454 --> 00:13:51,789
but I find it hard to trust you.

219
00:13:51,872 --> 00:13:53,624
Do you know what he did?

220
00:13:56,627 --> 00:13:59,797
Right. It's more important for the agency
that you stand out

221
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:00,923
than the drama, ma'am.

222
00:14:01,006 --> 00:14:03,717
"Ma'am"?

223
00:14:04,134 --> 00:14:06,011
Right.

224
00:14:14,812 --> 00:14:15,646
It's his job.

225
00:14:15,729 --> 00:14:18,899
Does his job need him to say
that she's pretty?

226
00:14:19,191 --> 00:14:20,943
I read the scenario.

227
00:14:21,026 --> 00:14:22,570
You're perfect for the role.

228
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:24,530
You majored in dancing,
so you don't need lessons.

229
00:14:24,613 --> 00:14:27,074
Plus, you've been toning yourself,
so you have a better figure now.

230
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:30,411
Right.

231
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:33,247
-It's fine.
-You're speaking casually to her.

232
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:36,041
-No, I'm on your side, Seon-ju.
-You're on her side?

233
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:39,962
If you ask me, I think it's time

234
00:14:40,045 --> 00:14:42,089
that you film a movie instead of a drama.

235
00:14:42,172 --> 00:14:44,633
And you're the production company's
first pick, so we still have time.

236
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:46,135
Let's not rush.

237
00:14:48,804 --> 00:14:51,181
Stop being so weak. You're doing great.

238
00:14:51,265 --> 00:14:52,808
You have two great options,

239
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:55,144
so let's give it some thought together
until this week.

240
00:14:55,227 --> 00:14:56,896
Hey!

241
00:14:56,979 --> 00:14:58,981
Let us think!

242
00:14:59,148 --> 00:15:01,859
I've said this so many times already!

243
00:15:02,276 --> 00:15:04,320
Why would you call me at this hour
for that?

244
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:05,571
Do you call this a worry?

245
00:15:06,071 --> 00:15:07,197
Do you call yourself an actress?

246
00:15:07,364 --> 00:15:09,158
Don't call me so late!

247
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:10,951
I'm hanging up!

248
00:15:15,789 --> 00:15:17,791
And you call that "flirting"?

249
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:20,669
I'm sure he let her on
more than necessary.

250
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:24,089
I'm not sure, but isn't Min-jun
the type of guy you can trust?

251
00:15:24,173 --> 00:15:25,758
He secretly likes to flirt.

252
00:15:25,841 --> 00:15:27,134
No woman would say no to that.

253
00:15:27,217 --> 00:15:28,969
I'm going to go kill her.

254
00:15:29,219 --> 00:15:31,680
Why would you kill her
when it's Min-jun that flirts?

255
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:35,059
Don't try to reason with me.

256
00:15:35,351 --> 00:15:38,812
This is so annoying.
I haven't thought this far.

257
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:40,689
Of course, they have actresses there too.

258
00:15:40,898 --> 00:15:42,191
Should I bring him back?

259
00:15:42,983 --> 00:15:44,902
What if he's with her now?

260
00:15:45,194 --> 00:15:46,362
MIN-JUN

261
00:15:50,282 --> 00:15:52,242
CHAIRMAN KIM

262
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:01,085
Delete them right now.

263
00:16:02,419 --> 00:16:03,420
What?

264
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:07,967
What are you doing?

265
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:11,220
Delete them.

266
00:16:11,387 --> 00:16:12,846
I asked, what are you doing?

267
00:16:13,430 --> 00:16:14,890
I meant to send them to my niece.

268
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:16,308
Her name is Eun-jeong.

269
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:18,394
Delete them. Right now.

270
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:22,231
Don't boss me around.

271
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:23,440
I deleted them.

272
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:25,025
No, you didn't.

273
00:16:26,193 --> 00:16:27,486
It's your fault you sent them to me.

274
00:16:27,945 --> 00:16:30,823
It's your fault your name
is Lee Eun-jeong. Delete them now.

275
00:16:31,281 --> 00:16:32,533
I did delete them.

276
00:16:37,204 --> 00:16:38,372
No, you didn't.

277
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:39,748
What is he doing?

278
00:16:40,374 --> 00:16:42,126
-Why? What is it?
-What?

279
00:16:44,878 --> 00:16:46,255
Nothing. Just work.

280
00:16:49,883 --> 00:16:50,968
One moment.

281
00:16:52,553 --> 00:16:53,554
Delete them right now.

282
00:16:56,223 --> 00:16:58,976
I'm with So-min now.
Shall I show them to her?

283
00:16:59,476 --> 00:17:00,477
No.

284
00:17:01,854 --> 00:17:03,439
Say, "Please delete them."

285
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:06,358
Please delete them.

286
00:17:07,901 --> 00:17:09,820
Say, "Thank you."

287
00:17:12,614 --> 00:17:13,699
Thank you.

288
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:18,662
Be polite like this from now on.

289
00:17:19,663 --> 00:17:21,623
Okay. Did you delete them?

290
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:24,126
I'll just show these to her.

291
00:17:24,209 --> 00:17:25,461
I'm sorry.

292
00:17:27,004 --> 00:17:28,881
-Is work that fun?
-Yes.

293
00:17:30,174 --> 00:17:31,175
It's Director Hey.

294
00:17:32,051 --> 00:17:34,511
Oh, my gosh. Is he crazy?

295
00:17:34,845 --> 00:17:35,846
What is he doing?

296
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:38,057
Does he do drugs?

297
00:17:41,518 --> 00:17:44,313
Wait. Why is he exchanging these photos
with you?

298
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:46,440
He meant to send them to his niece.

299
00:17:46,523 --> 00:17:47,649
Her name is Eun-jeong.

300
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:51,236
Still, it means your name was
at the top of his recent call names.

301
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:53,322
Well, I interviewed him.

302
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:54,490
Right.

303
00:17:55,991 --> 00:17:58,035
Can you send these to me?

304
00:17:58,619 --> 00:18:00,329
He's completely nuts.

305
00:18:00,412 --> 00:18:02,539
I can't believe he sticks his tongue out
and acts cute.

306
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:04,833
He seemed to like kids.

307
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:06,376
He donates all the money he makes,

308
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:09,046
and he goes to an orphanage to eat
because he doesn't want to buy rice.

309
00:18:09,129 --> 00:18:10,964
What a weirdo.

310
00:18:12,341 --> 00:18:14,635
He's weird but nice.

311
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:17,846
No. He's weird but good.

312
00:18:18,639 --> 00:18:20,516
No. He's just weird.

313
00:18:20,599 --> 00:18:22,976
Send them to me now.
I'm going to tease him.

314
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:25,687
No. I happen to have something on him,

315
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:27,564
so let me use this for my interview.

316
00:18:27,648 --> 00:18:29,608
-You did it already.
-He gave short answers,

317
00:18:29,691 --> 00:18:30,943
so I can't use anything.

318
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:32,194
Get it done quickly.

319
00:18:32,486 --> 00:18:34,113
I'm going to show it to him
whenever he yells.

320
00:18:36,073 --> 00:18:37,533
How far do you think you can write?

321
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:41,745
We'll be able to finish up to Episode ten
before the shoot.

322
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:43,705
We actually have more time now
than before,

323
00:18:43,789 --> 00:18:45,874
so it's not a big deal for us.

324
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:47,167
I'm worried about the shoot.

325
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:49,419
I'm not going to work less hard
just because I'm in a rush.

326
00:18:49,503 --> 00:18:51,588
Don't worry about the shoot.

327
00:18:51,672 --> 00:18:54,174
Just do your work like you're doing now.

328
00:18:54,842 --> 00:18:56,009
I'm good.

329
00:18:57,344 --> 00:19:00,222
He makes me trust him naturally
without begging.

330
00:19:00,722 --> 00:19:04,143
That's what it seemed like,
but we've seen the variables.

331
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:06,186
You said that before the presentation.

332
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:07,729
That's the only thing I'm not good at.

333
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:09,481
I can never get better.

334
00:19:10,065 --> 00:19:13,110
It's time for the general meeting.

335
00:19:14,069 --> 00:19:15,070
Let's go.

336
00:19:16,572 --> 00:19:18,365
Jae-hun, you should leave first.

337
00:19:18,448 --> 00:19:21,118
I need to talk to Ms. Lim
about the script.

338
00:19:21,201 --> 00:19:22,536
Okay.

339
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:25,247
-Do you have time, Ms. Lim?
-Sure.

340
00:19:25,330 --> 00:19:27,040
-Let's get going then.
-Okay.

341
00:19:27,124 --> 00:19:28,709
-See you later.
-See you.

342
00:19:28,792 --> 00:19:30,127
-See you later.
-Bye.

343
00:19:34,089 --> 00:19:36,800
The assistant director will
join you tomorrow.

344
00:19:36,884 --> 00:19:39,887
And I have some requests for you, Su-hui.

345
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:42,514
We checked the scripts in advance
as we're running out of time.

346
00:19:42,598 --> 00:19:45,809
These things will be flagged
once the scripts are reviewed.

347
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:47,144
But this is...

348
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:50,272
It won't be as fun
if you take out all the swear words.

349
00:19:50,439 --> 00:19:51,607
I know it from my experience,

350
00:19:51,690 --> 00:19:54,067
but I'm sure "son of a bitch" is allowed.

351
00:19:54,151 --> 00:19:56,737
-It can't be directed at someone.
-But you can say it to yourself?

352
00:19:56,820 --> 00:19:58,822
You can, but you can't keep saying it.

353
00:19:58,906 --> 00:20:01,867
"You punk, you fool, you jerk."

354
00:20:01,950 --> 00:20:03,035
Is that what they want?

355
00:20:03,368 --> 00:20:06,288
To make this world
a pure one without swear words,

356
00:20:06,371 --> 00:20:09,208
let us put our hearts together...

357
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:11,960
Have you not seen how schoolkids swear
these days?

358
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:14,504
Their voices haven't broken
but they are worse than adults.

359
00:20:14,588 --> 00:20:17,299
They didn't learn that from TV.

360
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:20,802
How about we outright swear on TV?

361
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:23,055
If we make it repulsive,
they might stop swearing.

362
00:20:23,138 --> 00:20:26,225
I get the feeling that it might help
make this society purer.

363
00:20:26,308 --> 00:20:29,144
Right. To make a purer society,

364
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:30,604
let's give up on TV.

365
00:20:30,687 --> 00:20:32,773
Let them swear only on TV.

366
00:20:33,190 --> 00:20:34,191
That's

367
00:20:35,025 --> 00:20:37,110
not something you should offer to me.

368
00:20:37,819 --> 00:20:40,113
You should form a group of people
with the same belief

369
00:20:41,782 --> 00:20:43,659
and go to Korea Communications Commission,

370
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:46,912
the Blue House, or the National Assembly,

371
00:20:46,995 --> 00:20:49,289
and go on a protest

372
00:20:49,373 --> 00:20:52,709
or write up a national petition.

373
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:55,170
That'd be faster.

374
00:20:55,254 --> 00:20:58,006
How many people do you think
will agree to my petition

375
00:20:58,090 --> 00:21:00,300
asking us to allow cursing on TV?

376
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:02,094
Another petition will be up,

377
00:21:02,177 --> 00:21:04,554
asking Ms. Lim Jin-ju to be expelled.

378
00:21:04,638 --> 00:21:06,390
More than 200,000 people will agree

379
00:21:06,473 --> 00:21:08,308
and the Blue House will respond
to it officially.

380
00:21:09,351 --> 00:21:10,936
-Will I be expelled?
-Yes.

381
00:21:11,019 --> 00:21:13,146
I kind of want to try it.

382
00:21:13,230 --> 00:21:17,526
We'll start shooting soon.
Please stop those scary thoughts.

383
00:21:19,486 --> 00:21:21,321
Since we're tight on schedule,

384
00:21:21,405 --> 00:21:23,949
if you could keep the due for the scripts,

385
00:21:24,032 --> 00:21:27,494
it'll be very much appreciated.

386
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:29,871
And this.

387
00:21:30,205 --> 00:21:33,792
These are the product placement offers.

388
00:21:34,042 --> 00:21:37,838
Please check if you can include this
in your script.

389
00:21:37,921 --> 00:21:41,258
I believe you can do it.

390
00:21:42,217 --> 00:21:43,218
No.

391
00:21:44,553 --> 00:21:46,138
-Ms. Lim?
-No.

392
00:21:46,221 --> 00:21:47,764
What kind of friends are we?

393
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:49,266
Friends like any other.

394
00:21:49,349 --> 00:21:52,102
We're still friends, so I'll count on you.

395
00:21:53,770 --> 00:21:55,063
Lovely.

396
00:22:01,361 --> 00:22:05,073
-Gosh.
-I trust you.

397
00:22:05,866 --> 00:22:09,244
Jeon Jo Mun-su is confirmed to be
the musical director.

398
00:22:09,328 --> 00:22:12,956
But we haven't decided on his pay yet,
so I'm heading to Plan D Studio now.

399
00:22:13,957 --> 00:22:16,960
And I'll finish signing contracts
with the head staff within this week.

400
00:22:17,794 --> 00:22:18,795
Okay.

401
00:22:19,755 --> 00:22:21,465
All right.

402
00:22:25,844 --> 00:22:27,637
IN-GUK'S DAD

403
00:22:30,891 --> 00:22:32,225
Hello?

404
00:22:34,227 --> 00:22:35,228
What is it?

405
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:40,650
In-guk doesn't have time this week.

406
00:22:40,734 --> 00:22:42,486
You always call me out of the blue.

407
00:22:42,569 --> 00:22:44,029
We're busy too.

408
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:48,241
What?

409
00:22:57,918 --> 00:23:01,129
It's harder to write
because I think I'm running out of time.

410
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:03,882
Right? Same here.

411
00:23:04,382 --> 00:23:06,968
Something is off. It's too ordinary.

412
00:23:07,052 --> 00:23:10,305
This really must be the beginning.
Are you nervous?

413
00:23:11,014 --> 00:23:13,683
But wasn't I good at pretending
to be laid-back?

414
00:23:13,767 --> 00:23:17,062
Yes. You're not letting them catch you.
Great job.

415
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:22,442
I keep thinking of Ms. Jung these days.

416
00:23:23,318 --> 00:23:26,905
"What would she do at a time like this?
How would she deal with this?

417
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:28,949
How did she do this?"

418
00:23:29,032 --> 00:23:31,993
She was annoying,
but she did give us useful advice.

419
00:23:32,077 --> 00:23:33,078
Right.

420
00:23:34,955 --> 00:23:36,498
Let's try to remember.

421
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:39,126
Let's try to remember.

422
00:23:39,209 --> 00:23:41,711
It seemed okay when you were writing,
so you kept on going.

423
00:23:41,795 --> 00:23:44,840
But when you are done,
it's just so ordinary.

424
00:23:45,257 --> 00:23:48,552
If you think it's special, your eyes,
your sensory organs are not working.

425
00:23:48,635 --> 00:23:51,555
You're not special.
You're ordinary. It's a fact.

426
00:23:51,638 --> 00:23:53,265
Don't think the opposite. You're wrong.

427
00:23:53,348 --> 00:23:55,851
What should we do now?

428
00:23:55,934 --> 00:23:58,603
Fix it. Your script gets better
the more you fix it.

429
00:23:58,687 --> 00:24:01,940
If it gets worse after your amendments,
then you have no talent.

430
00:24:02,023 --> 00:24:04,109
You're not qualified. Quit then.

431
00:24:04,401 --> 00:24:07,821
So what do we need now?

432
00:24:11,449 --> 00:24:13,869
My ability as a writer?

433
00:24:13,952 --> 00:24:15,745
That's a given.

434
00:24:15,829 --> 00:24:18,165
I'm not here to talk about
something so obvious.

435
00:24:19,666 --> 00:24:21,251
The reason to give up?

436
00:24:22,544 --> 00:24:24,921
What you need is time.

437
00:24:25,005 --> 00:24:26,923
The time to re-write.

438
00:24:27,799 --> 00:24:30,677
Then what do you need to earn more time?

439
00:24:31,386 --> 00:24:33,889
-Diligence.
-And?

440
00:24:33,972 --> 00:24:35,056
And...

441
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:41,855
It's too hard.

442
00:24:45,233 --> 00:24:47,485
-Guts.
-Guts?

443
00:24:48,236 --> 00:24:51,740
Don't let anyone including the director
intimidate you. Fight head-on.

444
00:24:52,115 --> 00:24:55,202
They are as anxious as you are.

445
00:24:55,410 --> 00:24:57,787
So think about how to improve your script

446
00:24:57,954 --> 00:24:59,289
if you have time to be intimidated.

447
00:25:01,291 --> 00:25:03,126
But you have to be intimidated by me.

448
00:25:07,714 --> 00:25:09,216
-Let's just write.
-Okay.

449
00:25:11,551 --> 00:25:12,886
Let's trust the director.

450
00:25:13,136 --> 00:25:15,096
-Our director.
-Okay.

451
00:25:16,223 --> 00:25:19,517
The layout of the set.
We've changed it as you suggested.

452
00:25:19,601 --> 00:25:22,646
We need you to confirm it by today
to meet the deadline.

453
00:25:22,729 --> 00:25:23,813
That's Ju-yeon's house.

454
00:25:24,648 --> 00:25:27,859
I wanted to have the full view
of the living room from the entrance.

455
00:25:29,069 --> 00:25:30,278
How much of it?

456
00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:32,864
What do you mean?
The house isn't that big.

457
00:25:33,114 --> 00:25:34,366
The full view of the living room.

458
00:25:34,699 --> 00:25:36,034
Oh, the living room.

459
00:25:36,576 --> 00:25:39,287
Okay. "Full view of the living room."

460
00:25:39,371 --> 00:25:41,873
Mr. Son, this is the list of car scenes.

461
00:25:41,957 --> 00:25:44,292
Will you film them in a tow truck
or on the set?

462
00:25:44,376 --> 00:25:46,044
-The set for many lines.
-All of them?

463
00:25:46,127 --> 00:25:47,545
-On the set on hot days.
-It's summer.

464
00:25:47,629 --> 00:25:49,464
-The set.
-Okay.

465
00:25:49,547 --> 00:25:50,840
Drama is all about the set.

466
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:52,759
-Set.
-Well.

467
00:25:52,842 --> 00:25:54,719
This is the styling concept sent from

468
00:25:54,803 --> 00:25:56,179
Ju-yeon and Sin-ae.

469
00:25:58,223 --> 00:26:00,350
Tell them not to doll up. Keep it natural.

