00:28:11,648 --> 00:28:13,525
-I'd write five pages a day.
-Okay.

517
00:28:13,608 --> 00:28:15,402
Let's say there are 40 pages per episode.

518
00:28:15,485 --> 00:28:17,904
-I should've finished one in eight days.
-Right.

519
00:28:17,987 --> 00:28:20,532
But why haven't I finished an episode
after 15 days?

520
00:28:20,615 --> 00:28:22,325
Because you didn't keep the promise.

521
00:28:35,588 --> 00:28:39,551
I've been sitting here for hours,
but why haven't I written a page?

522
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:43,513
How could I spend the whole day
on writing a line?

523
00:28:43,596 --> 00:28:45,390
Because that's all you think about.

524
00:28:46,391 --> 00:28:47,809
It's 6 p.m. I should get off work.

525
00:28:47,892 --> 00:28:50,603
You're not planning to finish your quota
but going home.

526
00:28:50,687 --> 00:28:52,605
I promised myself to get off work at six.

527
00:28:52,689 --> 00:28:54,899
So why is that the only promise you keep?

528
00:28:55,608 --> 00:28:58,486
I should keep the promise I can. Bye.

529
00:28:59,779 --> 00:29:01,364
What does that even mean?

530
00:29:06,661 --> 00:29:08,621
Look at this punk.

531
00:29:09,164 --> 00:29:12,041
He's been leaving me alone
saying he's busy.

532
00:29:18,339 --> 00:29:20,008
Should we make employee ID cards

533
00:29:20,091 --> 00:29:21,760
-for the network staff?
-We should.

534
00:29:21,843 --> 00:29:23,553
-Should we add photos too?
-Yes.

535
00:29:23,636 --> 00:29:25,597
Should they be ID photos?

536
00:29:25,930 --> 00:29:28,391
What else? Family photos?

537
00:29:28,516 --> 00:29:29,809
Some people use selfies.

538
00:29:40,528 --> 00:29:42,447
Let's take a five-minute break.

539
00:29:43,907 --> 00:29:45,492
Let's have some coffee.

540
00:29:46,159 --> 00:29:47,494
-What do you say?
-Buy us some coffee.

541
00:29:47,577 --> 00:29:48,745
Sure. What do you want?

542
00:30:01,132 --> 00:30:03,551
-Hello?
-I want to see you.

543
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:04,969
That's good.

544
00:30:05,804 --> 00:30:08,598
But I guess the same thing
isn't happening to you.

545
00:30:08,681 --> 00:30:11,768
I'm dying to see you.
Can't you hear how anxious I am?

546
00:30:11,851 --> 00:30:12,852
It doesn't sound that bad.

547
00:30:12,936 --> 00:30:15,271
Come on. My hands shook in the morning
because I needed sugar,

548
00:30:15,355 --> 00:30:17,440
and now, they shake because I need you.

549
00:30:17,524 --> 00:30:19,192
Hand tremor has become
an on-going condition.

550
00:30:19,275 --> 00:30:22,821
But what can I do? I should work.
It's our project.

551
00:30:23,446 --> 00:30:26,324
Don't try to get away
with your sweet talk.

552
00:30:27,826 --> 00:30:29,828
You always say that.

553
00:30:30,411 --> 00:30:32,580
All right. Go back to your meeting.

554
00:30:32,664 --> 00:30:36,167
Okay. Don't skip your meal. Eat slowly.

555
00:30:37,043 --> 00:30:38,169
Smooch, smooch.

556
00:30:38,711 --> 00:30:39,963
Captain fart!

557
00:30:40,797 --> 00:30:43,091
I'm proud of you.

558
00:30:46,302 --> 00:30:47,303
Okay.

559
00:30:48,388 --> 00:30:50,640
Okay. Enjoy your dinner.

560
00:30:51,266 --> 00:30:53,726
All right. I'll call you later. Bye.

561
00:31:03,444 --> 00:31:05,029
Laugh or something.

562
00:31:06,281 --> 00:31:07,282
What's the matter?

563
00:31:08,408 --> 00:31:10,076
Why are you staring at me?

564
00:31:17,917 --> 00:31:19,460
He doesn't want to see this?

565
00:31:20,253 --> 00:31:21,588
Is that even possible?

566
00:31:22,672 --> 00:31:25,800
Fine. I'll approach this
from a man's point of view.

567
00:31:37,020 --> 00:31:38,980
I told you not to come to my work.

568
00:31:40,815 --> 00:31:41,816
Ms. Hwang.

569
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:43,526
Had you told me to come,
I wouldn't have come.

570
00:31:43,860 --> 00:31:45,737
You still don't know me.

571
00:31:45,820 --> 00:31:47,655
Why should I know you?

572
00:31:47,739 --> 00:31:49,282
I know a quiet cafe nearby.

573
00:31:49,365 --> 00:31:50,533
I know one too.

574
00:31:53,411 --> 00:31:54,787
Someone should give him a ticket.

575
00:32:07,467 --> 00:32:09,427
I can't stay for long. Be quick.

576
00:32:10,136 --> 00:32:12,055
Let the coffee cool first.

577
00:32:12,138 --> 00:32:13,806
Let it cool while you talk.

578
00:32:19,103 --> 00:32:20,188
Look at this.

579
00:32:24,609 --> 00:32:26,569
Did you call me here
to brag about your house?

580
00:32:29,155 --> 00:32:31,908
I built a house in Jeju Island.

581
00:32:32,951 --> 00:32:35,745
There's too much fine dust here.

582
00:32:35,954 --> 00:32:38,665
To think that In-guk is breathing
and running around

583
00:32:38,748 --> 00:32:40,458
in this city...

584
00:32:42,168 --> 00:32:43,336
It's not right.

585
00:32:47,048 --> 00:32:48,841
You want to take In-guk?

586
00:32:49,300 --> 00:32:51,803
Do you want to die?
I can kill you right here.

587
00:32:53,930 --> 00:32:55,139
You've changed a lot.

588
00:32:55,932 --> 00:32:56,975
That's good.

589
00:32:57,934 --> 00:33:01,062
How could I take In-guk from you?

590
00:33:01,646 --> 00:33:03,940
I... Well...

591
00:33:06,234 --> 00:33:07,402
How about

592
00:33:09,153 --> 00:33:11,155
-we live together?
-What?

593
00:33:11,239 --> 00:33:13,908
I mean, I know apologizing for what I did

594
00:33:14,075 --> 00:33:16,411
won't make you forgive me.

595
00:33:16,619 --> 00:33:18,871
That's why I'd like to make up for it

596
00:33:19,038 --> 00:33:22,250
for the rest of my life.

597
00:33:22,333 --> 00:33:26,629
If you give me the last chance, that is.

598
00:33:29,549 --> 00:33:31,384
Why are you being like this
all of a sudden?

599
00:33:31,467 --> 00:33:33,886
It's not all of a sudden.
I thought about this for long.

600
00:33:33,970 --> 00:33:36,305
Why did you think about this for long?

601
00:33:36,389 --> 00:33:38,725
I've lost my faith in you.

602
00:33:38,808 --> 00:33:40,727
Be as honest as you can,

603
00:33:40,810 --> 00:33:43,354
then maybe I'll consider listening to you.

604
00:33:49,652 --> 00:33:52,071
To tell you the truth,

605
00:33:53,698 --> 00:33:54,699
I am...

606
00:33:57,910 --> 00:33:59,162
a bit sick.

607
00:34:00,872 --> 00:34:02,373
I'm not sure if I'll be cured.

608
00:34:04,250 --> 00:34:05,543
I don't know.

609
00:34:05,626 --> 00:34:06,627
What?

610
00:34:12,842 --> 00:34:14,886
You're the worst.

611
00:34:16,554 --> 00:34:17,764
So you're sick?

612
00:34:18,848 --> 00:34:20,767
-Is that why?
-I'm sorry.

613
00:34:21,851 --> 00:34:23,311
I know I'm shameless.

614
00:34:23,394 --> 00:34:24,896
So you need a caregiver now?

615
00:34:24,979 --> 00:34:26,230
It's not like that.

616
00:34:26,773 --> 00:34:29,025
I have enough money to hire a caregiver.

617
00:34:29,108 --> 00:34:31,360
Fine. Go on.

618
00:34:31,819 --> 00:34:34,322
How sick are you? Are you dying?

619
00:34:34,697 --> 00:34:35,698
Well...

620
00:34:40,495 --> 00:34:42,246
Why are you doing this to me?

621
00:34:44,123 --> 00:34:45,124
Why...

622
00:34:46,584 --> 00:34:48,711
Why are you ruining my life?

623
00:34:50,046 --> 00:34:52,882
What did I do so wrong to you?

624
00:34:55,426 --> 00:34:57,762
I'll receive treatments. I'll get better.

625
00:34:58,721 --> 00:35:01,766
I'll have to change my constitution
to cure rhinitis.

626
00:35:02,183 --> 00:35:04,477
It's hard to fully recover.

627
00:35:04,560 --> 00:35:05,561
What?

628
00:35:11,067 --> 00:35:12,485
-"Rhinitis"?
-Yes.

629
00:35:13,611 --> 00:35:15,404
It's getting worse.

630
00:35:15,738 --> 00:35:18,407
I can't use toilet roll
because it has a lot of dust.

631
00:35:18,658 --> 00:35:20,409
I can only use facial tissues.

632
00:35:20,993 --> 00:35:22,995
And it costs quite a lot.

633
00:35:24,580 --> 00:35:27,542
To think that this is all
because of fine dust...

634
00:35:45,268 --> 00:35:49,480
I made a mistake talking
for too long with you.

635
00:35:49,939 --> 00:35:52,066
It's my fault. Right.

636
00:35:53,901 --> 00:35:54,902
I'll get going.

637
00:35:57,655 --> 00:35:59,282
I'm not done talking.

638
00:35:59,991 --> 00:36:01,325
Why are you leaving all of a sudden?

639
00:36:03,035 --> 00:36:05,496
I meant it when I said I want
to get back with you.

640
00:36:34,108 --> 00:36:35,526
I'm sorry.

641
00:36:35,610 --> 00:36:37,570
I'm a junior member of staff
at Ms. Hwang's company.

642
00:36:37,653 --> 00:36:40,656
It's my job to take care of
her unfinished business.

643
00:36:41,199 --> 00:36:42,200
You can sue me.

644
00:36:56,339 --> 00:36:57,423
I'm sorry.

645
00:37:00,509 --> 00:37:04,138
I'm sorry. I got worried and followed you.

646
00:37:05,264 --> 00:37:07,350
Why were you worried?

647
00:37:08,434 --> 00:37:12,855
All the weird things that are around you.

648
00:37:14,190 --> 00:37:17,568
He is a weirdo indeed.

649
00:37:18,152 --> 00:37:19,320
I'm sorry.

650
00:37:19,487 --> 00:37:22,365
He's still In-guk's dad. Out of impulse...

651
00:37:22,448 --> 00:37:23,908
Don't worry.

652
00:37:24,450 --> 00:37:28,913
He's usually good at dodging
and running away.

653
00:37:29,872 --> 00:37:32,416
It's really hard to hit him. Great job.

654
00:37:34,377 --> 00:37:36,879
But what if he actually sues you?

655
00:37:37,546 --> 00:37:39,131
Then it happens.

656
00:37:42,009 --> 00:37:46,097
How did you punch him
to knock him down like that?

657
00:37:48,140 --> 00:37:50,434
Well, the jaw.

658
00:37:52,061 --> 00:37:53,271
The jaw?

659
00:37:54,021 --> 00:37:56,148
Just below the mouth.

660
00:38:00,236 --> 00:38:03,364
Anyway, this is how I feel.

661
00:38:05,908 --> 00:38:07,451
I can't let you go.

662
00:38:10,913 --> 00:38:11,998
Thanks.

663
00:38:13,124 --> 00:38:15,167
Hold on tight so I can't go.

664
00:38:16,085 --> 00:38:17,086
Okay.

665
00:38:31,559 --> 00:38:34,895
Is that what you call
"approaching from a man's point of view"?

666
00:38:34,979 --> 00:38:37,523
Yes. Men are weak
when it comes to pretty women.

667
00:38:37,815 --> 00:38:39,483
I'm pretty enough already,

668
00:38:39,567 --> 00:38:41,777
but given the situation,
I need to become prettier.

669
00:38:41,861 --> 00:38:43,446
What kind of situation is that?

670
00:38:44,822 --> 00:38:46,615
Work is taking my boyfriend away from me.

671
00:38:50,244 --> 00:38:51,579
It sounds serious.

672
00:38:51,662 --> 00:38:52,955
Is it?

673
00:38:53,164 --> 00:38:56,125
Yes. Men like to make
working sound really important.

674
00:38:56,208 --> 00:38:57,918
"Let me off. I'm working."

675
00:38:58,002 --> 00:38:59,545
They think it's only right
to think that way.

676
00:38:59,628 --> 00:39:00,629
Why do they do that?

677
00:39:01,630 --> 00:39:05,051
It's part of the instinct they had
when they had to hunt in the past.

678
00:39:05,134 --> 00:39:07,428
Why is their instinct so behind time?

679
00:39:07,511 --> 00:39:09,847
Ask them to keep up.

680
00:39:09,930 --> 00:39:11,599
I'll try.

681
00:39:12,933 --> 00:39:15,144
-I put In-guk to sleep.
-Thanks.

682
00:39:16,729 --> 00:39:17,980
Don't you want any beer?

683
00:39:18,814 --> 00:39:20,691
Something happened to her, right?

684
00:39:23,152 --> 00:39:25,446
You're right. Something happened,

685
00:39:25,696 --> 00:39:28,532
but let me gather my thoughts
before talking to you.

686
00:40:11,492 --> 00:40:14,745
Gosh, he isn't the only one who works.

687
00:40:34,723 --> 00:40:37,059
-Hi, Ms. Lim.
-Are you still at work?

688
00:40:37,143 --> 00:40:40,688
Yes. I'm looking for some clips
I can use as a reference.

689
00:40:40,771 --> 00:40:43,232
-It's late. What did you do today?
-I don't know.

690
00:40:43,315 --> 00:40:44,608
You don't know what you did today?

691
00:40:44,692 --> 00:40:47,361
No, I don't. I'm going to sleep. Bye.

692
00:40:48,154 --> 00:40:50,823
You must be tired. Goodnight.

693
00:41:11,177 --> 00:41:14,096
Gosh, this is bad.

694
00:41:14,513 --> 00:41:15,556
All right.

695
00:41:15,806 --> 00:41:17,850
I'm letting him off the hook today.

696
00:41:20,060 --> 00:41:21,103
Damn it. That fool.

697
00:41:26,066 --> 00:41:29,195
Since we'll have to start shooting
outdoor first,

698
00:41:29,278 --> 00:41:31,655
we took some photos of the location.

699
00:41:31,906 --> 00:41:34,909
This can be the alleyway
around Ju-yeon's house.

700
00:41:35,367 --> 00:41:36,368
Here.

701
00:41:37,828 --> 00:41:39,371
Wait, that's...

702
00:41:40,372 --> 00:41:41,540
-Go back.
-Okay.

703
00:41:41,624 --> 00:41:43,334
-One more.
-Okay.

704
00:41:43,626 --> 00:41:46,295
I think I saw this photo
for the last drama.

705
00:41:48,297 --> 00:41:49,215
Are you reusing it?

706
00:41:49,298 --> 00:41:52,343
Oh, I opened the wrong folder.

707
00:41:52,426 --> 00:41:55,971
No, you didn't. You just opened Things
Will Be Fine Once You Turn Thirty.

708
00:41:56,055 --> 00:41:59,934
Oh, I named the folder wrong.

709
00:42:04,688 --> 00:42:08,901
We need to discuss
the concept of our shoot too.

710
00:42:09,777 --> 00:42:11,070
Let's schedule another meeting.

711
00:42:11,153 --> 00:42:13,614
So-min is shooting a documentary now.

712
00:42:13,697 --> 00:42:16,283
Can she bring a cameraman with her?

713
00:42:16,367 --> 00:42:18,869
Sure. As long as it doesn't get leaked
before it gets aired.

714
00:42:18,953 --> 00:42:22,456
Okay. And it seems we'll have to
create Team B.

715
00:42:22,540 --> 00:42:24,250
Do you have anyone in mind?

716
00:42:24,333 --> 00:42:25,376
Yes, I do.

717
00:42:28,921 --> 00:42:30,172
I want you to be my Team B.

718
00:42:32,591 --> 00:42:35,219
Do you mean it? How can I?

719
00:42:35,302 --> 00:42:37,388
-Just do it. I don't have time.
-But...

720
00:42:37,471 --> 00:42:39,306
Stop annoying me. Be quiet.

721
00:42:39,890 --> 00:42:41,225
I'm glad you acknowledge my--

722
00:42:41,308 --> 00:42:43,894
I do acknowledge that you have
a lot of free time.

723
00:42:43,978 --> 00:42:47,815
I'm about to lose my mind,
so don't talk to me.

724
00:42:49,483 --> 00:42:50,484
Okay.

725
00:42:53,946 --> 00:42:54,947
Beom-su.

726
00:42:56,490 --> 00:42:58,367
Can you let me talk to you about my worry?

727
00:42:58,450 --> 00:43:02,162
You're going to talk about Da-mi again.
Is she your only kind of worry?

728
00:43:02,246 --> 00:43:04,373
Yes. I just want to know.

729
00:43:04,456 --> 00:43:08,294
Why is it so hard to reach her at night?

730
00:43:08,377 --> 00:43:10,004
Go and ask her yourself.

731
00:43:10,087 --> 00:43:11,338
-She says she slept.
-Then she did.

732
00:43:11,422 --> 00:43:14,216
Well, she could call me
before going to bed, right?

733
00:43:14,300 --> 00:43:16,552
One time, we were texting
but she wouldn't answer her phone.

734
00:43:16,635 --> 00:43:18,137
-What's that about?
-I don't know.

735
00:43:18,220 --> 00:43:22,099
She started nitpicking and said
she's too upset to talk.

736
00:43:22,182 --> 00:43:24,393
You should've behaved better
so she wouldn't nitpick you.

737
00:43:24,476 --> 00:43:26,895
-So I should've been perfect.
-Yes.

738
00:43:28,314 --> 00:43:30,733
Try to talk to her and see what's wrong.

739
00:43:30,816 --> 00:43:34,320
I tried, but whenever I do, I lose.

740
00:43:34,403 --> 00:43:36,572
I always end up apologizing.

741
00:43:37,323 --> 00:43:38,907
All I want to know

742
00:43:40,284 --> 00:43:41,994
is why she doesn't answer her phone.

743
00:43:42,077 --> 00:43:44,788
I don't know.
How in the world would I know that?

744
00:43:46,582 --> 00:43:47,791
Hey, both you and I.

745
00:43:47,875 --> 00:43:50,127
We're respected here as directors,

746
00:43:50,210 --> 00:43:51,337
but outside,

747
00:43:51,462 --> 00:43:54,214
we're just two lame guys.

748
00:43:54,298 --> 00:43:56,759
But you're better than me.
You're in Team A and I'm in B.

749
00:43:56,842 --> 00:43:59,720
Go and tell Da-mi your worry
as if it were mine.

750
00:43:59,803 --> 00:44:02,640
She wouldn't know it's about her
and start giving advice.

751
00:44:02,723 --> 00:44:05,768
Come on.
Of course, she'll know it's about her.

752
00:44:05,851 --> 00:44:08,729
She loves to talk. I'm sure she won't.

753
00:44:16,028 --> 00:44:18,614
I decided to manage Beom-su's Team B.

754
00:44:19,490 --> 00:44:20,783
Will you be all right with that?

755
00:44:21,408 --> 00:44:22,993
The schedule has been moved up,

756
00:44:23,077 --> 00:44:25,579
so at least he'll need a reliable Team B.

757
00:44:26,997 --> 00:44:29,416
Why would he need a reliable team?

758
00:44:31,001 --> 00:44:33,962
I think he's got some problems
with his girlfriend as well as work.

759
00:44:34,588 --> 00:44:36,799
That's why the director and the writer

760
00:44:36,882 --> 00:44:38,967
shouldn't have gotten hooked
before the drama is over.

761
00:44:39,259 --> 00:44:42,596
Why? What kind of problem?

762
00:44:43,305 --> 00:44:44,890
Never mind. It's his business.

763
00:44:44,973 --> 00:44:48,602
How can we not mind it?
It's our friend's business.

764
00:44:48,852 --> 00:44:51,980
I read 26 magazines a month.
I'm the expert here. Tell me.

765
00:44:52,064 --> 00:44:54,983
It's nothing serious.
He can't reach her at night.

766
00:44:55,067 --> 00:44:56,568
Maybe she went to bed a couple of times...

767
00:44:56,652 --> 00:44:59,696
It's common. It's so obvious.

768
00:44:59,780 --> 00:45:01,657
-Is it?
-There's always a reason.

769
00:45:01,740 --> 00:45:03,951
She doesn't pick up because she can't.

770
00:45:04,034 --> 00:45:05,202
There are only three cases

771
00:45:05,285 --> 00:45:06,870
where one can't answer the phone at night.

772
00:45:06,954 --> 00:45:07,913
Three cases?

773
00:45:07,996 --> 00:45:11,250
When you're bedridden, mourning,
