00:45:15,546 --> 00:45:19,258
That's right. And you can't be ill
or be at a funeral all the time.

776
00:45:19,341 --> 00:45:21,135
You don't give a shit
when he's your boyfriend?

777
00:45:21,218 --> 00:45:22,928
That just doesn't make sense.

778
00:45:23,303 --> 00:45:24,513
Then what does it mean?

779
00:45:24,680 --> 00:45:28,016
It means she was doing something
that she's not very proud of.

780
00:45:28,100 --> 00:45:30,811
Like going out drinking with guys

781
00:45:30,894 --> 00:45:32,729
or going clubbing.

782
00:45:37,818 --> 00:45:40,737
-Did I just get fooled?
-If that's how you feel.

783
00:45:44,074 --> 00:45:46,410
Well, that's me.

784
00:45:46,618 --> 00:45:48,328
I went out to drink.

785
00:45:48,829 --> 00:45:52,082
I make plans with my friends
every quarter.

786
00:45:52,166 --> 00:45:53,917
I couldn't cancel those plans,

787
00:45:54,001 --> 00:45:55,836
and it hasn't been long
since we started dating.

788
00:45:55,919 --> 00:45:59,590
If I kept going out,
it'd make me look bad.

789
00:46:00,090 --> 00:46:02,301
That's why I avoided your calls and lied.

790
00:46:02,384 --> 00:46:04,428
I'm sorry. I won't do it anymore.

791
00:46:05,053 --> 00:46:08,599
Okay. Well, it's fine.

792
00:46:08,932 --> 00:46:10,851
-It's understandable.
-Don't get disappointed.

793
00:46:10,934 --> 00:46:13,729
-Okay.
-Go on and work on your Team B.

794
00:46:14,521 --> 00:46:15,564
Okay.

795
00:46:24,740 --> 00:46:26,617
It feels iffy but relieving.

796
00:46:27,868 --> 00:46:31,330
It feels relieving but iffy.

797
00:46:32,581 --> 00:46:36,543
I won but why does it feel like I lost?

798
00:46:57,481 --> 00:46:59,441
MR. SON

799
00:47:03,779 --> 00:47:04,863
Are you busy?

800
00:47:13,997 --> 00:47:16,625
In a meeting. I'll call you after this.

801
00:47:23,966 --> 00:47:25,842
-It's 6 p.m.
-I'll work as well.

802
00:47:26,635 --> 00:47:28,387
Does he think I have nothing to do?

803
00:47:29,513 --> 00:47:30,597
Come on.

804
00:47:43,402 --> 00:47:44,736
MR. SON

805
00:47:47,739 --> 00:47:49,032
Yes, Mr. Son.

806
00:47:49,908 --> 00:47:51,034
What are you doing?

807
00:47:53,036 --> 00:47:54,079
I'm working.

808
00:47:54,830 --> 00:47:55,872
I'm sorry.

809
00:47:57,040 --> 00:48:00,043
-For what?
-For asking that too late.

810
00:48:01,503 --> 00:48:03,088
It's more annoying that you know it.

811
00:48:03,171 --> 00:48:06,008
Right. I understand. I apologize.

812
00:48:06,091 --> 00:48:09,678
Forget it. What are you doing anyway?

813
00:48:10,512 --> 00:48:13,890
I was watching the audition clips
and didn't realize the time.

814
00:48:15,183 --> 00:48:17,144
-Did you eat?
-No.

815
00:48:17,227 --> 00:48:20,230
Shall we go to eat something nice
and go for a walk?

816
00:48:21,982 --> 00:48:24,151
I'll consider it in a positive light.

817
00:48:25,152 --> 00:48:26,236
Thank you.

818
00:48:32,784 --> 00:48:33,869
I'm getting off work.

819
00:48:45,756 --> 00:48:49,217
Just be nice to me.
I don't need you to be shy.

820
00:48:49,301 --> 00:48:50,594
Is that so?

821
00:48:51,345 --> 00:48:52,304
Come in.

822
00:49:02,814 --> 00:49:04,983
When I look at So-min's eyes,

823
00:49:05,067 --> 00:49:08,695
it feels like they are
asking me questions.

824
00:49:09,029 --> 00:49:10,614
How should I put this?

825
00:49:11,907 --> 00:49:14,034
They are innocent and full of curiosity.

826
00:49:14,868 --> 00:49:16,995
They are like those of a smart kid

827
00:49:17,079 --> 00:49:20,248
who wants to find out the answer herself
instead of asking the adults.

828
00:49:21,249 --> 00:49:24,461
She's basically innocent
and has a passion for her work.

829
00:49:24,544 --> 00:49:26,630
And I'm grateful

830
00:49:26,713 --> 00:49:28,799
that I get to work with someone like her.

831
00:49:38,058 --> 00:49:39,851
You could've been like this before.

832
00:49:41,103 --> 00:49:42,062
Thank you.

833
00:49:51,113 --> 00:49:52,280
I deleted them.

834
00:49:52,364 --> 00:49:54,783
-No, you didn't.
-Yes, I did.

835
00:49:56,368 --> 00:49:57,703
Do you want some beer?

836
00:50:01,331 --> 00:50:03,250
Don't you get cute with me.

837
00:50:13,510 --> 00:50:15,637
It's not that I'm trying to save my money.

838
00:50:15,929 --> 00:50:18,098
I had some great snacks at the studio.

839
00:50:19,099 --> 00:50:20,267
It's dried smelt.

840
00:50:21,101 --> 00:50:22,102
Try it.

841
00:50:34,573 --> 00:50:36,450
-It's good.
-Do you want to take some?

842
00:50:36,533 --> 00:50:37,826
I have a lot at my studio.

843
00:50:39,286 --> 00:50:41,329
Do you know
that being nice actually suits you?

844
00:50:41,413 --> 00:50:44,750
Of course. I'm doing my best to be nice.

845
00:50:44,916 --> 00:50:46,168
It's really uncomfortable,

846
00:50:46,251 --> 00:50:48,044
but my superhuman power
is helping me get through.

847
00:50:48,128 --> 00:50:50,338
Those photos were no big deal.
They were cute.

848
00:50:50,422 --> 00:50:51,339
I don't like cute.

849
00:50:51,423 --> 00:50:53,091
You like kids, but you don't like cute?

850
00:50:53,175 --> 00:50:55,010
I don't want to be cute.

851
00:50:55,135 --> 00:50:56,261
-That's cute.
-No.

852
00:50:56,344 --> 00:50:58,305
-You're cute.
-Damn it.

853
00:51:00,265 --> 00:51:03,518
Can't you be nice when you work too?

854
00:51:03,602 --> 00:51:06,772
Does yelling or cursing
make things better?

855
00:51:06,855 --> 00:51:08,023
I can't control myself.

856
00:51:08,899 --> 00:51:11,234
That's why I say something
they don't understand.

857
00:51:11,985 --> 00:51:13,737
It's not about the language.

858
00:51:13,820 --> 00:51:15,822
They can feel the energy.

859
00:51:18,742 --> 00:51:19,743
Sorry?

860
00:51:19,951 --> 00:51:21,745
They won't understand me in Africa.

861
00:51:22,829 --> 00:51:24,956
I'm going to go to Africa.

862
00:51:27,125 --> 00:51:29,085
Are you going to see the children?

863
00:51:33,548 --> 00:51:36,510
I'm going to stay until I get sick
of them this time.

864
00:51:36,593 --> 00:51:38,094
So I'm saving up.

865
00:51:38,220 --> 00:51:40,722
How can you save up
when you keep donating?

866
00:51:41,973 --> 00:51:45,644
I actually wanted to ask you something.

867
00:51:45,936 --> 00:51:47,479
At the orphanage...

868
00:51:48,855 --> 00:51:50,023
I mean,

869
00:51:52,943 --> 00:51:55,153
it was easy to breathe there.

870
00:51:56,738 --> 00:51:59,199
What's there to ask?

871
00:52:00,492 --> 00:52:02,869
Just feel what you feel.

872
00:52:04,412 --> 00:52:05,497
Right.

873
00:52:06,581 --> 00:52:08,500
-Thanks.
-For what?

874
00:52:09,709 --> 00:52:11,837
I don't know. I just feel that way.

875
00:52:22,973 --> 00:52:24,015
Then...

876
00:52:25,058 --> 00:52:26,101
Gosh.

877
00:52:27,978 --> 00:52:29,688
What's the big deal?

878
00:52:30,897 --> 00:52:32,190
God.

879
00:52:35,861 --> 00:52:36,862
Here.

880
00:52:39,698 --> 00:52:40,949
I've deleted them all.

881
00:52:41,199 --> 00:52:42,033
What about the copies?

882
00:52:42,117 --> 00:52:44,953
Come on. We're not in a crime film.

883
00:52:50,750 --> 00:52:53,336
I'm finished. See you later.

884
00:52:53,753 --> 00:52:56,172
Delete them from your memories too.

885
00:53:08,351 --> 00:53:09,728
LEE SO-MIN

886
00:53:13,315 --> 00:53:14,316
Director.

887
00:53:25,035 --> 00:53:27,078
-How fast can you run 100m?
-15 seconds.

888
00:53:27,162 --> 00:53:28,872
You're really fast.

889
00:53:50,352 --> 00:53:53,229
You've been a bit upset
since yesterday, haven't you?

890
00:53:54,397 --> 00:53:55,398
No.

891
00:53:56,775 --> 00:53:59,945
"Upset" makes me sound petty.

892
00:54:01,363 --> 00:54:03,198
Then how should we describe this?

893
00:54:04,199 --> 00:54:05,867
Something that's along the same line.

894
00:54:06,368 --> 00:54:10,288
I'm looking at you in a negative light.
That would do.

895
00:54:11,414 --> 00:54:13,625
I see.

896
00:54:15,251 --> 00:54:16,836
So you're hurt.

897
00:54:19,464 --> 00:54:22,467
I was crazy busy.
I had to confirm every single thing.

898
00:54:22,717 --> 00:54:24,052
That's an excuse.

899
00:54:27,514 --> 00:54:30,350
I don't see why this is an excuse.

900
00:54:30,767 --> 00:54:33,520
I had to work.
It's not like I met my friends

901
00:54:33,603 --> 00:54:35,522
or drank all night long.

902
00:54:36,272 --> 00:54:39,025
I made the time to meet you
amidst my busy schedule.

903
00:54:40,527 --> 00:54:41,611
You made the time?

904
00:54:43,238 --> 00:54:46,616
Did that phrase upset you?

905
00:54:47,617 --> 00:54:50,912
You and I are both very busy.

906
00:54:52,163 --> 00:54:55,250
Isn't it great that we still manage
to make time for each other?

907
00:54:57,877 --> 00:55:00,296
I don't want to be someone

908
00:55:00,672 --> 00:55:02,966
my boyfriend needs to make
time to meet with.

909
00:55:03,049 --> 00:55:04,175
Should we not meet at all then?

910
00:55:04,259 --> 00:55:07,095
That's not what's important here.

911
00:55:07,178 --> 00:55:08,263
Gosh, this is frustrating.

912
00:55:08,847 --> 00:55:11,933
I understand it's hard to meet
if you're busy.

913
00:55:12,017 --> 00:55:15,395
But I'd hate that.
That's why I make time to see you.

914
00:55:15,520 --> 00:55:16,813
No, that's not what I mean.

915
00:55:17,272 --> 00:55:19,899
Whether we meet briefly
or don't meet at all,

916
00:55:19,983 --> 00:55:22,360
what matters is how we feel
for each other.

917
00:55:22,902 --> 00:55:27,490
I feel like you're treating me
like the laundry

918
00:55:27,907 --> 00:55:29,075
you've been procrastinating.

919
00:55:30,577 --> 00:55:32,287
How can you say that?

920
00:55:32,996 --> 00:55:34,622
Why would you talk like that?

921
00:55:36,374 --> 00:55:39,169
Laundry? Procrastinating?

922
00:55:43,465 --> 00:55:47,218
Gosh, you know that both of us are busy.
Why do you always let this upset you?

923
00:55:52,932 --> 00:55:53,933
"Always"?

924
00:55:54,976 --> 00:55:56,519
What do you mean, "always"?

925
00:55:58,563 --> 00:56:00,315
I never did this.

926
00:56:00,940 --> 00:56:02,192
This is my first time.

927
00:56:02,776 --> 00:56:03,777
You're right.

928
00:56:09,365 --> 00:56:13,995
Did I just get the baton
passed on from your ex-girlfriend?

929
00:56:14,079 --> 00:56:16,539
I made it sound misleading.

930
00:56:18,083 --> 00:56:20,001
I'm sorry. It's my bad.

931
00:56:20,627 --> 00:56:21,669
I'm sorry.

932
00:56:28,051 --> 00:56:30,637
I started at my own starting line.

933
00:56:31,054 --> 00:56:32,055
You're right.

934
00:56:33,389 --> 00:56:35,141
I'm going to be

935
00:56:35,767 --> 00:56:37,435
disappointed in you today.

936
00:56:39,395 --> 00:56:40,480
I'll get going.

937
00:56:53,660 --> 00:56:54,744
Ms. Lim.

938
00:56:56,746 --> 00:56:58,373
I'm sorry.

939
00:56:59,833 --> 00:57:02,794
If a human being didn't make
the same mistake repeatedly,

940
00:57:02,961 --> 00:57:06,047
it'd be the best to date
someone who's dated a lot of times.

941
00:57:06,339 --> 00:57:09,300
But then,
why did they end up dating so many times?

942
00:57:09,884 --> 00:57:12,595
Gosh,
I won't let the variables take me down.

943
00:57:13,054 --> 00:57:16,391
There are more good things
than bad things about you.

944
00:57:17,642 --> 00:57:19,436
Follow me already.

945
00:57:21,563 --> 00:57:24,274
-What?
-Why are you so far behind?

946
00:57:27,527 --> 00:57:30,029
Weren't we going to walk apart,

947
00:57:30,113 --> 00:57:31,990
go home, regret all night long,

948
00:57:32,073 --> 00:57:33,700
and apologize tomorrow?

949
00:57:36,870 --> 00:57:38,663
-Come to me.
-Sorry?

950
00:57:38,746 --> 00:57:40,123
I said to come to me.

951
00:57:40,957 --> 00:57:43,334
-You want me to come to you now?
-Should I go?

952
00:57:43,418 --> 00:57:46,421
I'm the generous one here.
Should I walk there too?

953
00:57:58,141 --> 00:57:59,142
What is this?

954
00:58:00,727 --> 00:58:03,646
I feel like I survived without doing much
at the brink of death.

955
00:58:04,898 --> 00:58:06,774
This is how generous I am.

956
00:58:07,025 --> 00:58:08,485
You're lucky.

957
00:58:10,945 --> 00:58:13,531
Since I met you, I've been thinking
maybe I saved the country

958
00:58:13,698 --> 00:58:16,493
in my previous life, but that wasn't it.

959
00:58:16,951 --> 00:58:20,288
I must have saved a lot more than that.
I must have been a hero.

960
00:58:21,039 --> 00:58:24,417
Gosh, a hero? You happy now?

961
00:58:27,587 --> 00:58:28,838
I'll never do it again.

962
00:58:28,922 --> 00:58:31,508
Of course, you won't.
Were you going to do it again?

963
00:58:35,887 --> 00:58:38,598
This is something In-guk shouldn't hear.

964
00:58:38,806 --> 00:58:40,558
So we'll whisper from now on.

965
00:58:47,815 --> 00:58:49,734
I met his dad.

966
00:58:51,778 --> 00:58:54,239
He wants to get back together.

967
00:58:55,490 --> 00:58:56,574
I'm thinking about it.

968
00:58:57,033 --> 00:58:58,451
Why would you even think about that?

969
00:58:59,911 --> 00:59:01,621
Don't tell me you're thinking about it.

970
00:59:03,748 --> 00:59:06,042
I should've just killed him then.

971
00:59:07,335 --> 00:59:10,129
Gosh, you really are thinking about it.
Are you crazy?

972
00:59:10,213 --> 00:59:14,133
Don't even think about it.
Just swear at him and forget about it.

973
00:59:14,717 --> 00:59:16,135
He was so fast.

974
00:59:16,219 --> 00:59:18,972
Don't get so emotional.

975
00:59:20,765 --> 00:59:24,727
Don't even think about it. Stop it.

976
00:59:24,894 --> 00:59:27,021
I'm going to cut our ties if you do.

977
00:59:27,105 --> 00:59:28,856
That's a bit too much.

978
00:59:30,316 --> 00:59:33,027
How can I not think about this?

979
00:59:33,111 --> 00:59:37,407
Why would you need to?
Do you still have feelings for him?

980
00:59:37,657 --> 00:59:39,826
-No, I don't!
-Then why?

981
00:59:39,909 --> 00:59:42,620
Wait. Things are getting too heated up.

982
00:59:43,121 --> 00:59:44,330
Calm down.

983
00:59:45,039 --> 00:59:47,625
So...

984
00:59:48,251 --> 00:59:51,504
Okay. Because you have In-guk,

985
00:59:52,088 --> 00:59:54,716
I know you can't think
only about yourself.

986
00:59:54,799 --> 00:59:56,634
I'm not saying she should only think
about herself.

987
00:59:56,718 --> 00:59:58,303
I'm saying she should put herself first.

988
00:59:58,386 --> 01:00:00,888
That's thinking about myself only.

989
01:00:00,972 --> 01:00:02,974
-It's different.
-How?

990
01:00:06,561 --> 01:00:10,523
It's just different,
so stop talking nonsense.

991
01:00:11,024 --> 01:00:13,568
Stop it. Let me hit him
from behind this time.

992
01:00:13,651 --> 01:00:16,487
I'll come with you.
Let's hit him from front and back.

993
01:00:19,073 --> 01:00:22,368
Hey, why won't you care about how I feel?

994
01:00:22,452 --> 01:00:24,746
You're telling me how you feel.

995
01:00:26,456 --> 01:00:28,333
Have you ever given birth to a child?

996
01:00:28,416 --> 01:00:29,959
Have you raised a child without his dad?

997
01:00:30,418 --> 01:00:32,920
Have you put yourselves in my shoes?

998
01:00:33,004 --> 01:00:34,339
Or In-guk's?

999
01:00:34,422 --> 01:00:37,133
Have you thought about how he lives
or how this would influence him?

1000
01:00:37,216 --> 01:00:39,510
That hurts.

1001
01:00:39,594 --> 01:00:41,346
We care about In-guk too.

1002
01:00:41,429 --> 01:00:42,764
If you do,

1003
01:00:43,556 --> 01:00:47,393
then you should seriously consider
these things.

1004
01:00:47,477 --> 01:00:50,229
Why are you telling me
not to even think about it?

1005
01:00:50,313 --> 01:00:53,900
It's because he doesn't deserve it.
He's not normal.

1006
01:00:54,400 --> 01:00:56,694
Don't badmouth In-guk's dad.

1007
01:00:57,236 --> 01:01:00,657
Are you ditching me
and taking his side now?

1008
01:01:00,823 --> 01:01:04,452
People could change over time, you know.

1009
01:01:05,244 --> 01:01:08,081
He asked you to get back together
just like that because he changed?

1010
01:01:08,164 --> 01:01:10,124
He never even tried.

1011
01:01:10,208 --> 01:01:11,626
He has no manners. He hasn't changed.

1012
01:01:11,709 --> 01:01:13,753
Why are you being so negative?

1013
01:01:13,836 --> 01:01:16,464
-Because he's a jerk.
-He is a jerk.

1014
01:01:18,466 --> 01:01:20,426
People don't change that easily.

1015
01:01:21,386 --> 01:01:23,721
And nothing changes what he did to you.

1016
01:01:25,264 --> 01:01:29,268
Now that the kid's grown up,
he's talking nonsense.

1017
01:01:29,352 --> 01:01:31,229
Tell him to get lost.

1018
01:01:31,312 --> 01:01:34,190
-I can never live with him.
-Of course not.

1019
01:01:34,273 --> 01:01:35,900
Wait.

1020
01:01:36,526 --> 01:01:38,653
Lower it down. You might wake him up.

1021
01:01:41,656 --> 01:01:42,907
Oh, we're whispering already.

1022
01:01:47,620 --> 01:01:48,496
It's become strange.

1023
01:01:48,579 --> 01:01:51,165
They were arguing,
but now they are on the same side.

1024
01:01:51,249 --> 01:01:55,670
Well, how did you form an ally
after swinging knives at each other?

1025
01:01:58,089 --> 01:01:59,173
What is this?

1026
01:02:00,675 --> 01:02:03,511
Why did you suddenly start agreeing to me?

1027
01:02:07,682 --> 01:02:08,850
Well, I...

1028
01:02:11,644 --> 01:02:14,522
I don't intend to find
my happiness in men.

